# Repository map (stressar-results)

Use this as the **orientation index** before searching the tree.

## Top-level

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `stressar-docs/` | Canonical Stressar specs: `RESULTS_FORMAT.md`, `METRICS.md`, `BENCHMARKING_GUIDE.md`, `README.md` (not a top-level `docs/`). |
| `results/` | Exported run bundles: one folder per run (`run_metadata.json`, `replica-*/summary.json`, `node_metrics/`, optional `report.md`). |
| `src/stressum/` | Installable package **`stressum`**: CLI + loaders + paper artifacts. |
| `tests/` | Pytest; synthetic bundle at `tests/fixtures/minimal-run/`. |
| `pyproject.toml` / `uv.lock` | `uv sync`; script entry `stressum = stressum.cli:main`. |

## stressum CLI

- **Comparison only:** `uv run stressum` or `uv run stressum --config …` — cross-scenario artifacts under `output/comparison-<timestamp>/` (see root `README.md`).

## Cross-rules

- **Bundle path meanings** when working under `results/**`: see `stressar-results-bundles.mdc`.
- **Metric semantics / aggregation**: `stressar-docs-reference.mdc` + files under `stressar-docs/`.
- **Code structure / module responsibilities**: `stressum-python-standards.mdc` (applies when editing `src/stressum/**` or `tests/**`).
